Build a full-stack production-ready web application called BarberSpotlight.

Overview

BarberSpotlight is a barber reservation platform where:

Customers do NOT need accounts

Customers can reserve a time slot at a barber shop

Barber shops DO have accounts and dashboards

Barber shops can manage availability, services, reservations and add staff 

Tech Stack (use best defaults)

Next.js (App Router)

TypeScript

Tailwind CSS

Prisma + PostgreSQL

Server Actions

Zod for validation

Shadcn/UI components

Authentication for barbers only (NextAuth or Clerk)

Core Features
1. Public Customer Flow (No Account)

Landing page explaining BarberSpotlight

3 Languages English, Albanian and German

3 currencies EUR,MKD and CHF (BARBERSHOPS CHOOSE WHEN CREATING THEIR SHOP)

Browse barber shops

View a barber shop profile:

Name

Location

Services (haircut, beard, combo, price, duration)

Available time slots

Reservation form:

Name

Phone number

Optional note

Select service

Select date & time

Submit reservation without logging in

Show confirmation screen after booking

2. Barber Authentication

Barber sign up

Barber login

Secure session handling

Each barber only sees their own data

3. Barber Dashboard

Create a protected dashboard for barbers with:

Dashboard Pages

Overview (todayâ€™s appointments, upcoming count)

Reservations list:

Customer name

Phone number

Service

Date & time

Status (pending, completed, canceled)

Ability to:

Cancel reservations

Mark as completed

Barber Management

Manage services:

Name

Price

Duration

Manage availability:

Working days

Opening & closing hours

Block off time slots

Backend Requirements

Prisma schema with:

Barber

BarberProfile

Service

Reservation

Availability

Server Actions for:

Creating reservations

Fetching available time slots

Barber CRUD operations

Prevent double bookings

Validate time slots against availability for each barber

Each barber staff has own time and date slots (depends on who customer picks)

UI / UX

Modern, clean barber-style design

Mobile responsive and ready

Use Shadcn components

Loading and error states

Toast notifications

